.TH hsh 1 "hsh man page" "1.0" "Dec 28 2025"
.SH NAME
simpleshell - Simple Shell written in C for Holberton School
.br

.SH SYNOPSIS
Simple Shell program that emulates a simpler sh command written in C.
.br

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple shell recreation, can execute programs as written commands.
.br
Once you start the program you will be met with a prompt to start typing a command, you can use a program's name or a program's path.
.br

.SH USAGE
This shell can be run in interactive mode, similiar to a command line interface. The "$ " prompt will appear when the user is asked for input and after a command has been executed.
.br

.RS
host@linux: ./hsh
.br
$ ls
.br
hsh main.c shell.c 
.br
$ls
.br
.RE

The program can also receive commands via piping (|), this the non-interactive mode.
.br

.RS
host@linux: echo "ls" | ./hsh
.br
hsh main.c shell.c
.br
host@linux:
.br
.RE

.SH BUILTINS
.B env
- prints the environment variables
.br
.B exit
- exits the program

